Build ID: M20060921-0945 (Fedora Core release 6 (Zod))

Steps To Reproduce:
1. Open an existing PHP project (this was possibly made in a previous version, but it happens for new projects as well)
2. Switch to PHP perspective, if not in it
3. Try to view the PHP explorer tab, but get error text inside the PHP explorer window itself (see more information for Exception information)

Additionally, if a PHP file is opened via the Navigator tab (one of, possibly, 100+ lines), it will lock the CPU and Eclipse will refuse to respond - at least 5 minutes.

I am reporting this error from a dual-core Pentium D system running 64-bit Fedora Core 6.  Additionally, this exact error happens on two other 64-bit systems of mine, running the same OS, but both are AMD Athlons, single cores.
